[
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.",
    "hash": "be9ed9bdd4ee8d2e364aac6db0cf190cb2761eacd18f79c546c9db13580a295b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of thine eye.",
    "hash": "eeff36624b736dfde12d2c9cbd16a89124518a9f8c534dbc299bf7abc8233827"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.",
    "hash": "d28a65507e094e118b97bd8ba90ea75fe410f84301159fc7d8395f6a194967a6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Say unto wisdom, Thou {art} my sister; and call understanding {thy} kinswoman:",
    "hash": "33e53002800e62bfc56cb0553754a760f9d5231dcce455f1ef93819833fa753c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger {which} flattereth with her words.",
    "hash": "265788fcb09f0bd14dde39f6bb2c3578384fc1d20e5f0a242eac03e8830c4019"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,",
    "hash": "fdea65548d691541f0269df24e9e21143c70a6ed6abe715e45a3e4f17f779447"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding, {the youths: Heb. the sons}",
    "hash": "c06f2dd4e24fb6607e4fc3219a487117bab9b49e3b0ee006b30119be54ff9628"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,",
    "hash": "6faf4d7511e0f3fe51258863984b91cac49d9c2cf7fb6d574fe7b2cf6018d56c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night: {in the evening: Heb. in the evening of days}",
    "hash": "9054cc99d5a1f12274191bcd35caa79acc4f5f5eb4421d5e9dda4caa6b9cd94a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And, behold, there met him a woman {with} the attire of an harlot, and subtil of heart.",
    "hash": "a6f9834f1265960e03d0ffb2d439a000ee66a7aca7322741cca9b4b636165838"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "(She {is} loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:",
    "hash": "0bf0a9deab6ce2bdfef3a9234a2d0edf7388dd06eae4c495b3072be74db4f892"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Now {is she} without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.)",
    "hash": "e565af293345f1af9a39ff51f06e3c19b411de6fe61690b770adf52709942b15"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "So she caught him, and kissed him, {and} with an impudent face said unto him, {with...: Heb. she strengthened her face and said}",
    "hash": "a1efc290218d713456ee47ba3fa18f488509572d43b68115643da2e14bb5eb3a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "{I have} peace offerings with me; this day have I payed my vows. {I have...: Heb. Peace offerings are upon me}",
    "hash": "f39e3e9bdc8e5da152dcda789b8e0092e9c875858562f100ca0654a3daa1f49a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.",
    "hash": "af59a3fb82d11dbe2ffd8cb0ed9580b5b79eaac6f5f30131e28541afe98b2b6a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with carved {works}, with fine linen of Egypt.",
    "hash": "48fe0ff111f45333727641d73e23e775c0d0783995605a81c4358d69cb82d4e4"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
    "hash": "b90b4c5dc98458b5e95258f7d2e8efe862576c66b37f99663efa74e2813ff543"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.",
    "hash": "64f979d81b30a9ccc959c608f7b9abba9650c8b31d4df5b1b449b1214ea2f9eb"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For the goodman {is} not at home, he is gone a long journey:",
    "hash": "57125bc0cde0ed072ad5f7582ce0a9f3445fc9f45e61e987b6c2e0df16b68aaf"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "He hath taken a bag of money with him, {and} will come home at the day appointed. {with...: Heb. in his hand} {the day...: or, the new moon}",
    "hash": "2c290f31aa1c35b3bdf311a623efe5803752b88297d81f39acd1d863655d9865"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "With her much fair speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she forced him.",
    "hash": "faa1727ed02e8d65e404caa5cf269a8604f362dfc03cab577b65abf277b39f45"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "He goeth after her straightway, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks; {straightway: Heb. suddenly}",
    "hash": "64fe2691dbfabd1a096b03bae6cbd32cb26d3233c6b5350b21d0f3751c12432c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Till a dart strike through his liver; as a bird hasteth to the snare, and knoweth not that it {is} for his life.",
    "hash": "f003702e11aa1dc89d8dad1ec8505277aade30c0f3fec56327d1e828bf060950"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Hearken unto me now therefore, O ye children, and attend to the words of my mouth.",
    "hash": "2bb1ff79b5898a59b42fa813ee9e46b22512f759ab73734dc41b5977207ae414"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Let not thine heart decline to her ways, go not astray in her paths.",
    "hash": "527d2e8a110a670b89f3b184a86b5f370b55f67e68a51f8cdc34864bd91d26de"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For she hath cast down many wounded: yea, many strong {men} have been slain by her.",
    "hash": "f7c67cbe077f86138235bf51cb29d69cb39654d45ff29ca781def07ce270e4b5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.7.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Her house {is} the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.",
    "hash": "3d5dc3ec47fb9bfefee12865720995bd5794e9f616f1caa23f3428e362560c3b"
  }
]